    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the deliberate scope limitation to quasi-static loading consistent with the static compression-bending regulatory submission. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the Accepted decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design verification use case. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) are satisfied for all primary QoIs. Project requirements for model fidelity and prediction accuracy are met as documented in the credibility assessment report.",
